collections.name: Dream Ruin
collections.description:
DREAM RUIN
"At the collision of reality and dreams, the mind begins to dissolve."

"Dream Ruin" explores the fragility of existence, the transformation of the human form, and the collapse of consciousness. Figures distort, landscapes dissolve, and dreams fragment into surreal ruins. The collection blends organic textures, fluid lines, and eerie compositions, capturing the moment when dreams disintegrate.

Technique & Style
Created through traditional and experimental techniques, this collection features:

Ink & Mixed Media for intricate textures,
Watercolor & Acrylic for fluid, dreamlike transitions,
Graphite & Charcoal for deep contrasts,
Layered Textures merging organic and mechanical forms.
"Dream Ruin" challenges artistic boundaries, visualizing the fragile threshold between dreams and reality.

collections.name: CarloSP_Landscapes
collections.description: Embark on a journey across the planet’s most breathtaking vistas in this curated collection of fine art landscape photographs. Each image—shot on a camera and edited in Adobe Photoshop—reflects a moment of pure, unaltered beauty. From the towering peaks of Torres del Paine to the tranquil shores of hidden alpine lakes, these photographs capture nature’s grandest displays. The play of light, shifting skies, and timeless allure of untamed wilderness converge to evoke both reverence and wonder. Every piece is a singular moment in time an unrepeatable convergence of weather, light, and perspective inviting you to pause, reflect, and immerse yourself in a realm where silence reigns and horizons extend into infinity. May this collection awaken your wanderlust and serve as a testament to the enduring power of our planet’s landscapes, as well as the stories they whisper to those who truly see.

collections.name: The 7 souls
collections.description:
​Embark on a journey into the heart of European forests with our exclusive collection, "The 7 Forest Animals." This series artfully intertwines the ecological roles of seven iconic creatures with the rich tapestry of European symbolism. Each illustration captures the essence of these animals, reflecting their significance in nature and their profound cultural meanings.​

From the instinctual prowess of the wolf to the transformative symbolism of the frog, this collection offers a unique perspective on the deep connection between nature and European folklore. Rendered in a captivating folk art style, each piece invites viewers to explore the stories and myths that have shaped our understanding of the natural world.​

Discover the beauty and depth of European symbolism through this unique collection, where art and nature converge to celebrate the timeless bond between humanity and the wild.

collections.description: DAARU BAAZ LADKI

Pandemic. Chaos and Silence.
　
In 2021, while the world remained lost in uncertainty and isolation, one man set out to document this era by filming the same bus stop every day.
　
From New Year's Day, for 365 days, the quiet resilience of life was captured—through rain and wind, in a place that seemed unchanged yet was never the same—even the subtlest shifts recorded with care.
　
Originally shared on Instagram, this project gathered over 6,600 followers and later became the film 2021, officially selected for AAIFF46 in New York in 2023, where it received recognition.
　
https://instagram.com/hayama_hayama
https://2021.world
　
This collection consists of 365 video works from the film 2021, each available in three editions.
　
The initial release includes Day 365 to Day 274 (December - October). The remaining works will be released in reverse order to emphasize time’s accumulation.
